cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on dense depth perception for autonomous driving and robotics applications, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel guided network for multi-modal feature fusion, which involves learning kernel weights from a guidance RGB image. This approach is related to deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational challenges of generating spatially-variant kernels, which could be addressed using convolution factorization. This aspect of the paper is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and their optimization.
